events.title: The Haydn Enthusiasts Present
events.description: Our inaugural concert, kicking off a cycle of 68.5 quartets

events.title: Concert 2: Opus 54
events.description: The first in a set of quartets dedicated to the violinist Johann Tost, these are some of Haydn's most interesting quartets with some virtuosic violin writing.

events.title: Opus 76: Peak Haydn
events.description: Come hear the most well-known quartets that Haydn wrote!

events.title: Opus 76: The Return
events.description: Come join us for the second installation of Haydn's brilliant Opus 76!

events.title: Haydn on the Fours
events.description: Come see the Haydn Enthusiasts play Opus 76, number 4 the string quartet called "Sunrise", paired with Opus 9 number 4, sometimes called Haydn's first great quartet! The quartets well be followed by a fashion show at Vessel Gallery!

events.title: Bookends: Haydn's Alpha & Omega
events.description: To end the year, we bring you Haydn's first great quartet, Opus 9#4, and his final complete quartet, Opus 77#2, written 30 years apart. Together, they bookend Haydn's productive and inventive career.

events.title: How do you do
events.description: Happy New Year everyone! We're jumping in with Haydn's Quartet Opus 33 #5, nicknamed "How do you do" and Opus 64 #4. We're going to be doing 6 pairings of Opus 33 and Opus 64 this year. Very interestingly, they are the only 2 sets of quartets that Haydn wrote that use all the same keys. They're kind of like "sister volumes" of quartets, separated in time by almost 10 years.

events.title: (Don't) B-minor
events.description: Continuing our sister Opus pairings of Opus 33 (1781) and Opus 64 (1790), we bring you two B-minor quartets, Opus 33#1 and Opus 64#2.

events.title: The Unofficial Jackalope
events.description: Continuing our "sister opus" pairings of Opus 33 (1781) and Opus 64 (1790), we bring you two B-flat Major quartets, Opus 33#4 and Opus 64#3. We have unofficially nicknamed Opus 33 #4 "The Jackalope's Progress". If you have nickname suggestions, we would love to hear them.
